latestPosts.caption:
JUNE MOODBOARD: Is it only me, or is June the strangest mix, the weirdest and somehow the best place to be?
Summer is here, but not quite. Everything good still feels ahead.
All I want to wear is something super relaxed: my favorite jeans, a tee, cool flip flops, and vintage sunnies.
But I’m also not ready to give up on my favorite layers (something I can never quite say goodbye to).
At the same time, there’s this wild urge to finally wear all my best summer dresses that have been patiently waiting all year — and now feels like the time for both.
The days stretch out, and you find yourself having long aperitivos outside, with no rush.
Plans for summer? Still undone - and that’s the beauty of it. Spontaneity feels luxe. (And I secretly love it)
Everything just feels softer, dreamier, a little undone — in the best way.

latestPosts.caption:
The layer I never put away — not even in spring or summer. This beigy mocha knit is the only one that works for me 12 months a year! In summer, it adds just the right layer and mood to anything: thrown over a tee, tied at the waist, or casually draped on your bag for a breezy night.
P.S. I also love leather too much to store it away. I keep my jackets and coats close all summer long, just in case you know
